	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: 240p test suite</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I recently added compression improvements that saved about 10 KiB:<br /><br /><ul><li>5.2 KiB by compressing help text with <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Byte_pair_encoding" class="postlink">digram tree encoding (DTE)</a>, the same text codec I used for <a href="https://github.com/pinobatch/rfk-nes" class="postlink">my robotfindskitten port</a></li><li>4.8 KiB by generating the Linearity with grid from Linearity without a grid instead of storing both</li></ul><br />This let me splurge a bit, adding more detail and color to the character on the help screens to match the GBC and GBA versions.

		
